node.title: Why You Sexually Repel Your Partner ⚡️❌

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on September 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, beard, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
I have recently been undergoing some changes that I would like to share with you.

When I started to “wake up” years ago, I cut everything out of my life.

And when I say everything, I mean everything. I didn’t even have a TV in my house. I went into deep isolation. I even moved into the mountains at one point.

I went through all of these different phases of shedding and growth to get to a place of being at peace with myself.

It was extremely dark at times.
I experienced loneliness, anxiety, depression, and lost many of my old friends.

I became so focused on being “spiritual” that I lost my sense of being human. I forgot what it felt like to be playful, to laugh, and to be FREE.

Lately, I have been feeling a deep pull to embody more of my authentic self.

I’ve always loved to have a good time. To see other people happy and laughing lights me up inside.

Even back in high school, I was always the kid having the parties because my heart has always yearned for connection. To bring people together and feel a sense of freedom through our ability to relate with one another.

Even if at the time, that relating was who could drink the most alcohol, lol.

Although I have changed some of my old bad habits, my core still remains the same.

My heart is big.
I care immensely for other people.
And I like to have a damn good time.

Here is what I have learned:

👉 Being “spiritual” or “conscious” doesn’t mean you bypass your human self.

👉 You can live a conscious life and still have fun.

👉 You don't need to be sitting in a cave, burning incense and chanting “om” to be spiritual.

👉 A major key to our freedom is found within our ability to release the illusion of being a “somebody” to fit into this world and be accepted.

Can I get a YES for the real people who are on this journey with me?

Much love,
-Jake

node.text:
🤔 “𝐀𝐬 𝐚 𝐦𝐚𝐧, 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐝𝐨 𝐈 𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠?”

If you feel like your woman is testing you, then this is when you must be the clearest with your direction and decision making. 

It may sound like her saying, “well, what do you think we should do?”

Or

“I am ok with whatever you decide.”

This is where a lot of men put the pressure back on her to make a decision.

But in this moment she is testing his clarity, direction, presence, + how grounded he is.

Resistance often starts because lack of direction in the relationship.

Women will often test a man to see if his masculine energy is sturdy enough to hold her.

As a masculine man you open the feminine through your:

Presence.
Humor.
Consistency.
Clear direction.
Unwavering confidence.
Grounded, heart connection.
Doing what you say you’re going to do.

👉 𝐖𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬? 𝐈 𝐠𝐨 𝐝𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐨𝐧 𝐦𝐲 𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐩𝐨𝐝𝐜𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐞𝐩𝐢𝐬𝐨𝐝𝐞 𝟐𝟑𝟐. 𝐈 𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐮𝐬𝐬 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠, 𝐝𝐫𝐲 𝐬𝐩𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐬, 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐭𝐨 𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐚 𝐬𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐝 𝐦𝐚𝐧. 𝐈𝐭’𝐬 𝐚𝐥𝐬𝐨 𝐨𝐧 𝐦𝐲 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐓𝐮𝐛𝐞 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐥...𝐠𝐨 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐤 𝐢𝐧 𝐦𝐲 𝐛𝐢𝐨 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐮𝐧𝐞 𝐢𝐧!

Sending you love,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jake Woodard on August 25, 2021 tagging @melissa_sgambelluri. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Can I be honest with you?

I was hesitant to post this.

Why?

Because I sometimes give way too many shits about what people might think about me.

Last night, I took my badass fiancé to the county fair.

I embraced my inner hillbilly.

I went on rides.
I played fair games.
I ate fair food.

And you know what?

I had a damn good time.

Because we all have that inner child within us that wants to play.

That wants to let go and be free.

There are too many people in the world who walk around with a constipated look on their faces.

Caring too much about what others think.
Afraid to speak how they feel.
Afraid to be their authentic self.

They are working their life away for nothing in return.

That used to be me.

Not anymore.

Who else loves to do things that make them feel like a kid again?

-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on August 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Many men struggle to connect deeply with a woman because they have unhealed mother wounds. He will continue to be triggered by women until he cuts the cord to the pain he carries from his mother. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
𝐀 𝐌𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫 𝐈𝐬 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐅𝐢𝐫𝐬𝐭 𝐖𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐀 𝐌𝐚𝐧 𝐋𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬

She has a significant impact on how he will relate with all women.

If he carries pain from his mother, he will likely resent the women he meets in life and not fully connect with them.

Here are a few examples of what this might look like.

A woman’s emotions or feelings easily trigger him.
He’s “clingy.”
He wants women to mother him and take care of him.
He struggles to express how he feels.
He’s emotionally unavailable.
He doesn’t respect a woman’s boundaries.

I struggled with a few of these things.

I didn’t realize for a while that I was carrying mother wounds.

When I took a deeper look, I noticed that some of the toxic patterns that manifested in my life stemmed from a mother wound.

It’s not easy to look within yourself and heal your pain. It takes extreme courage.

But I can tell you from personal experience that owning your shit, and healing it, will set you free.

-Jake

But they will be if you try to analyze and control her emotions

We men often complicate the f*ck out of most things, LOL

What do women really want?

A man who’s grounded.
A man who leads.
A man who has a meaningful mission.
A man who will commit to her.
A man who will protect her.
A man who’s strong and clear.

When he’s flying around like Peter Pan, her inner masculine gets activated.

She basically says, “I can’t trust this guy's masculine energy. It’s unsafe for me.”

She will start to wonder:

“Where is he leading me?”
“Can I trust his direction?”
“Can I fully open to him?”
“Why do I feel guarded with him?”

Now, let’s also consider this. If she has masculine wounds and her inner masculine is already activated, she will struggle to trust any man’s masculine energy.

And if she really wants to attract a conscious masculine man, her shield may be blocking her feminine magnetism, 𝐰𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐡 𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐥𝐲 𝐰𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐈 𝐭𝐞𝐚𝐜𝐡 𝐰𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐧 𝐢𝐧𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐦𝐲 𝐧𝐞𝐰 𝐜𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞, 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐌𝐚𝐠𝐧𝐞𝐭𝐢𝐜 𝐅𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞.

node.text:
🤔 𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐂𝐚𝐧’𝐭 𝐈 𝐀𝐭𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭 𝐀 𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐬𝐜𝐢𝐨𝐮𝐬 𝐌𝐚𝐧?

Years ago, I worked with a woman named Ashley.

She was a beautiful soul who yearned to connect with a man with who she felt aligned with.

At the time, she was in her mid-thirties and had gone through some pretty terrible relationships.

She was working a pretty intense corporate job demanding her to be in her masculine a lot.

She found herself pretty burned out from all of the mental focus, making decisions, leading, strategizing, and logical thinking.

When we started working together, I asked her what her relationship with masculine energy was like and if she trusted it.

She shared with me how when she was young, her father was pretty absent from her life.

She lacked a strong masculine figure to support, protect, and lead her.

As we dug in further, we started to uncover that she had been holding onto a masculine shield because she never felt safe expressing her feminine heart.

She was using excess masculine energy to protect her, support her and lead her.

Which was creating a huge imbalance within her personal life, health, and romantic relationships.

As we focused on cultivating more of her soft, gentle, intuitive, sensual, and loving feminine essence into her life, her energy started to shift.

A few months after we had finished working together, she told me that she had met a man.

She was amazed that she could rest in her feminine when she was with him because his masculine energy felt strong enough to hold her!

🔥 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗶𝘀 𝗲𝘅𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗹𝘆 𝘄𝗵𝘆 𝗜 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗱 𝗺𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝘄 𝗰𝗼𝘂𝗿𝘀𝗲, 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗠𝗮𝗴𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗰 𝗙𝗲𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗲. 𝗜 𝗱𝗲𝘀𝗶𝗴𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝘁𝗲𝗮𝗰𝗵 𝘄𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗻 𝗵𝗼𝘄 𝘁𝗼 𝗵𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿 𝗺𝗮𝘀𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲, 𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 𝗱𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗳𝗲𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲, 𝗿𝗲𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗶𝗿 𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗱𝘀𝗲𝘁, 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗰𝘁 𝗮 𝗺𝗮𝘀𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻.

1. Her romantic life struggles. If a woman has a feminine core (not all do, but most) and is constantly in her masculine, she will tend to emasculate men and attract feminine men.
2. Her nervous system is overloaded. The “busyness” of her mind makes her feel overwhelmed and stressed. Making decisions all day, planning, organizing, and strategizing doesn’t ignite the deep love that wants to flow through the feminine body.
3. She becomes very guarded. Unable to feel the life force energy that moves through her. All of her emotions, feelings, and sensuality become repressed. Which makes her constantly feel on edge and exhausted.

The feminine wants to FLOW.
She wants to DANCE.
She wants to FEEL.

🔥 This is exactly why I created my new course, The Magnetic Feminine. I’ve learned a lot from working with thousands of women over the years, and I packed all of that into a powerful online course.

This course teaches women how to heal their inner masculine, reprogram their dating mindset, activate their divine feminine essence, and attract a conscious masculine man.
